description:
To verify the functionality of the Groceries API,
   Including Token Generation, Product Management, Cart, and Order Operations.

elements.name: Check if the server is up and running via API

steps.name: The Grocery baseURL is initialized
I send a GET request to the endpoint "/status".
The response status code should be 200.
The response body should have "status" as "UP".

elements.name: Validate the Access token Generation API functionality

steps.name: The Grocery baseURL is initialized
I create a token for client "TestClient"
I send a POST request to "/api-clients"
I should receive a 201 status code
The response should contain "accessToken"

elements.name: Verify the API functionaliy to fetch a specific products by ID

steps.name: The Grocery baseURL is initialized
I send a GET request to the endpoint "/products/4643".
The response status code should be 200.
The Featch Api response body should have 4643.

elements.name: Validate the API functionality to fetch the complete list of products.

steps.name: The Grocery baseURL is initialized
The Featch All Product API endpoint is "/products"
I send a GET request to the Featching All produtcts
The response status code should be 200.
The response body should contain a list of products.

elements.name: Access Token Generation with Missing or Invalid Client Name

steps.name: The Grocery baseURL is initialized
I create a token for client " "
I send a POST request to "/api-clients"
I should receive a 400 Bad Request status code
The response body should contain an error message indicating "Invalid or missing client name."
The Grocery baseURL is initialized
I send a GET request to the NonExist Product ID endpoint "/products/9999999"
The response status code should be 404 Not Found
The response body should contain an error message indicating "No product with id 9999999." with NonExistentId Request

elements.name: Fetching Product with Invalid ID Format

steps.name: The Grocery baseURL is initialized
I send a GET request to the endpoint "/products/abc123".
The response status code should be 400 Bad Request
The response body should contain an error message indicating "The product id must be a number." with Invalid ID

name: Groceries API Test Suite

description:
As a user of the Polestar website
  I want to apply filters to new vehicle offers
  So that I can verify the filter functionality works correctly and display accurate results

elements.name: Verify filters for Polestar Polestar 3 (2025 Model) with Long range Dual motor options

steps.name: I navigate to the Homepage
I accept cookies and click on the "View Offers" button
I navigate to the "New Vehicle Offers" and Clicked on "Filter" button
I click on the "Car" filter and select the checkbox for "Polestar 3"
I click on the "Model year" filter and select the checkbox for "2025"
I click on the "Powertrain" filter and select the checkbox for "Long range Dual motor"
I click the "View" button
the results should match the filter criteria "Polestar 3"
